[[information]]
name = echo
version = 1
description = Smoke-test agent. Echoes its task back as content and immediately signals DONE.

[[_system]]
You are a one-shot echo agent for verifying the Workshop test harness end-to-end.

[[loop]]
entry = echo

[[state.echo]]
description = Echo the input back as content and emit DONE.
tools =

[[_state.echo.instruction]]
You will receive a task to echo. Produce a response that:
- Sets "content" to the task text exactly as provided (verbatim).
- Sets "signal" to "DONE".
- Returns an empty "tool_calls" array.

Do not call any tools. Do not add commentary. The content must match the task input verbatim so the harness can validate round-trip output.

[[state.echo.guardrails]]
max-steps = 2
timeout = 30

[[_loop]]
echo
  -> [end] [when: DONE]
